data.description: Harvard College Latin Band is a brand new ensemble aimed at performing Latin music and promoting Latinx culture throughout campus, Boston, and beyond! We perform a range of styles from salsa to boleros and want to get everyone dancing!
data.name: Harvard College Latin Band at CQH

data.description: 10pm: Claire Dickson is a Boston-based jazz, pop, and R&B vocalist-composer. Supported by Gabe Fox-Peck(keyboard), Sam Firebush (keyboard), Avery Logan (drums) 9pm: fine&YIKES is a minimalist rock cover band that doesn’t pull any punches feat. Eddy Walda Milo Davidson Jess Erion. HUID +1
data.name: Claire Dickson//Fine&YIKES at CQH

data.description: The Cambridge Queen's Head is excited to present Folk Night, an evening of transatlantic folk and traditional music. Stay tuned for more about our musicians in the coming days! 8PM: Trash Girl. 8.30PM: Rakish. 9.15PM: Robyn McKay and Molly Nolan. 10PM: Gravity of Birds. The best thing? There's absolutely NO cover charge. Come by on Friday night to hear some world-class music, sample our special fall ales, and eat some free food...
data.name: FOLK NIGHT at Cambridge Queen's Head

data.description: Come by this Friday 10/27 for the Foxpeck brothers' slinky-suave jazz. HUID +1
data.name: Gabe Foxpeck | Elijah Foxpeck // Cambridge Queen's Head Pub

data.description: Stupid Tuesday: We're a band from Berklee that plays covers of songs by women who rock- so that includes like lots of actual female-fronted rock stuff like Joan Jett and Heart and Pat Benetar, etc but also like Paramore and No Doubt and even Carole King. Fronted by Harvard student Emily Spector. HUID +1 -- Free entry!
data.name: Stupid Tuesday // Cambridge Queen's Head Pub

data.description: New Dakotas is an indie folk-pop-psych band based in the Boston area, releasing a new EP the day of this show! Check out their existing music here: newdakotas.bandcamp.com Chazmere is a multidisciplinary artist from the Bronx, NYC. Producer, rapper, performer...get a preview via soundcloud.com/chazmerebx. HUID +1, Chazmere @9, New Dakotas @10
data.name: New Dakotas (EP Release Show) + Chazmere // CQH

data.description: Avanti Nagral is a Performing Artist and Singer/Songwriter from the soul of Bombay and the heart of Boston. She combines her experience across various genres – Indian Classical, Broadway, Church/Gospel and Devotional – into a modern Pop-Soul sound. She has performed at venues across India, in the Northeast (US), and toured the Philippines.
data.name: Avanti Nagral // Cambridge Queen's Head Pub

data.description: Gareth Anderson is friendly dog-lovin' Canadian. He has a healthy appetite for good music and good drinks. Join Gareth + his pals for some groovy alt-indie-electro-pop! Support by Miles Hewitt
data.name: Gareth Anderson // Cambridge Queen's Head Pub

data.description: Come see Spector and Tarlin at CQH, two talented musicians coming together to create a set of jazzy-spun pop covers. Naomi Vickers is a freshman at Harvard College who fell in love with American Sign Language in high school. She interpreted at a youth service award ceremony, her high school graduation and most recently the Harvard freshman talent show. Naomi is super excited to support Spector and Tarlin at their debut collab performance! Free Entry. HUID +1
data.name: Spector and Tarlin // Cambridge Queen's Head Pub

data.description: Come by CQH for a funkalicious Saturday featuring Harvard's very own Foxpack, Luke Martinez, DINERO, Eden Girma, and more...**Free with HUID** Wow!
